00:14:38.247 --> 00:14:40.330
Leptin, which is a hormone
you've likely heard of,

00:14:40.330 --> 00:14:43.851
in the Latin, it's
leptos, which means thin.

00:14:43.851 --> 00:14:45.850
It is produced in the
short term in the stomach,

00:14:45.850 --> 00:14:49.390
and the long term in the
adipocytes or fat cells.

00:14:49.390 --> 00:14:53.590
And it is also anorexigenic
and promotes satiety,

00:14:53.590 --> 00:14:55.570
that feeling of fullness.

00:14:55.570 --> 00:14:57.910
CCK or cholecystokinin
is produced

00:14:57.910 --> 00:14:59.770
in the small intestine.

00:14:59.770 --> 00:15:01.400
It promotes early satiety.

00:15:01.400 --> 00:15:03.520
So you get full quicker.

00:15:03.520 --> 00:15:07.570
And also, it plays a role
in digestive enzymes,

00:15:07.570 --> 00:15:10.210
and release of acid
in the stomach.

00:15:10.210 --> 00:15:12.640
Finally, we have
peptide YY, which

00:15:12.640 --> 00:15:15.580
is produced in the last part of
the small intestine, the ileum,

00:15:15.580 --> 00:15:17.650
and the colon, which
is the large intestine.

00:15:17.650 --> 00:15:21.520
And it promotes satiety,
so it is also anorexigenic.

00:15:21.520 --> 00:15:23.257
