What I do find that
works pretty effectively

01:06:52.640 --> 01:06:54.680
for these individuals
are weight loss

01:06:54.680 --> 01:06:57.110
pharmacotherapy for
those individuals that

01:06:57.110 --> 01:06:59.210
have mild or moderate obesity.

01:06:59.210 --> 01:07:02.000
And then for those that have
severe weight loss surgery,

01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:05.270
I would entertain if
they're in those ranges.

01:07:05.270 --> 01:07:07.760
Often, they come in with
these very virtuous diets.

01:07:07.760 --> 01:07:09.815
The dietitian is like,
I can't change anything.

01:07:09.815 --> 01:07:12.900
Psychologist is like, everything
looks good on their part.

01:07:12.900 --> 01:07:15.680
And so then we have to
start to begin to think

01:07:15.680 --> 01:07:17.010
of other treatment strategies.

01:07:17.010 --> 01:07:19.010
And I think about
using the right tool

01:07:19.010 --> 01:07:20.550
for the size of the problem.

01:07:20.550 --> 01:07:23.192
So people are like, really,
weight loss surgery?

01:07:23.192 --> 01:07:24.650
Isn't that a method
of last resort?

01:07:24.650 --> 01:07:26.483
That's kind of a pet
peeve when I hear that.

01:07:26.483 --> 01:07:28.260
Because we think about--

01:07:28.260 --> 01:07:30.590
I kind of use an analogy
of snow in Boston.

01:07:30.590 --> 01:07:32.570
We get 14 inches in eight hours.

01:07:32.570 --> 01:07:34.670
Do I go to use a
teaspoon or a tablespoon

01:07:34.670 --> 01:07:35.980
to scoop up the snow?

01:07:35.980 --> 01:07:38.649
Maybe it would work, but it's
going to take me a long time.

01:07:38.649 --> 01:07:40.190
I'm going to use
the appropriate tool

01:07:40.190 --> 01:07:41.357
for the size of the problem.

01:07:41.357 --> 01:07:43.190
So I'm going to probably
use a big bulldozer

01:07:43.190 --> 01:07:44.780
to bulldoze the
snow out of the way

01:07:44.780 --> 01:07:48.020
so that the traffic
can continue.

01:07:48.020 --> 01:07:50.711
And I use the appropriate tool
for the size of the problem.

01:07:50.711 --> 01:07:51.960
Some people need bigger tools.

01:07:51.960 --> 01:07:53.610
Some people need smaller tools.

01:07:53.610 --> 01:07:56.930
Some people, hey,
I lost 80 pounds

01:07:56.930 --> 01:07:58.550
from just removing
sugar from my diet.

01:07:58.550 --> 01:07:59.610
Great for them.

01:07:59.610 --> 01:08:00.110
Excellent.

01:08:00.110 --> 01:08:01.190
But just because
it worked for you,

01:08:01.190 --> 01:08:02.700
doesn't mean it's going to
work for the next person.

01:08:02.700 --> 01:08:05.699
And so I have to tune into
what works for that individual,

01:08:05.699 --> 01:08:07.490
and use the right tool
for that individual.

01:08:07.490 --> 01:08:08.990
And recognize that
that's malleable,

01:08:08.990 --> 01:08:11.750
meaning what tool
may have worked today

01:08:11.750 --> 01:08:13.490
may not always
work continuously,

01:08:13.490 --> 01:08:15.080
and I get to keep adding.

01:08:15.080 --> 01:08:16.700
Much like-- I can't remember
the individual that said,

01:08:16.700 --> 01:08:17.825
oh we have to keep trying--

01:08:17.825 --> 01:08:19.140
where's that lovely-- you.

01:08:19.140 --> 01:08:21.140
You're like, we have
to keep doing things?

01:08:21.140 --> 01:08:23.740
Yes, you have to
sometimes keep trying.

01:08:23.740 --> 01:08:25.439
It's nice when I can
just do one thing,

01:08:25.439 --> 01:08:27.720
and then I solve their
problem, which means

01:08:27.720 --> 01:08:28.970
that I didn't really solve it.

01:08:28.970 --> 01:08:30.410
I'm just treating the problem.

01:08:30.410 --> 01:08:33.529
But often, it requires
a lot of different steps

01:08:33.529 --> 01:08:34.700
that I'm having to take.

01:08:34.700 --> 01:08:37.279
And working through
all of the motion that

01:08:37.279 --> 01:08:40.340
goes into this person
struggling with weight.

01:08:40.340 --> 01:08:41.319
So yeah.

01:08:45.985 --> 01:08:46.609
She's one more.

01:08:46.609 --> 01:08:47.817
I can hear you, you can talk.

01:08:47.817 --> 01:08:49.291
- [INAUDIBLE]

01:08:49.291 --> 01:08:49.790
- Go on.

01:08:49.790 --> 01:08:50.289
OK.

01:08:54.210 --> 01:09:02.750
- OK, I'd like to suggest
that another indicator--

01:09:02.750 --> 01:09:06.590
cause-- might be
growing up feeling

01:09:06.590 --> 01:09:09.260
silenced for political reasons.

01:09:09.260 --> 01:09:11.170
And therefore, eating.

01:09:11.170 --> 01:09:18.630
And even after one works on
its ramifications in therapy,

01:09:18.630 --> 01:09:23.840
I don't think it's necessarily
easy to then just kind of lose

01:09:23.840 --> 01:09:25.399
the weight off, right?

01:09:25.399 --> 01:09:31.939
I mean, after dealing
with emotional issues,

01:09:31.939 --> 01:09:34.880
if one has been obese
all their life--

01:09:34.880 --> 01:09:35.840
- Has obesity.

01:09:35.840 --> 01:09:37.236
You don't never classify it.

01:09:37.236 --> 01:09:38.634
You have the disease.

01:09:38.634 --> 01:09:40.140
You're not classified by it.

01:09:40.140 --> 01:09:41.899
It does not govern you.

01:09:41.899 --> 01:09:42.649
- Yeah.

01:09:42.649 --> 01:09:47.149
So how does that work?

01:09:47.149 --> 01:09:49.340
- I think the question is
surrounding-- and just,

01:09:49.340 --> 01:09:50.590
you can tell me if I'm right--

01:09:50.590 --> 01:09:52.319
is if you've had a life--

01:09:52.319 --> 01:09:54.500
because I'm going
to kind of group

01:09:54.500 --> 01:09:57.650
it into people that have
had lifelong struggles.

01:09:57.650 --> 01:09:59.700
I have people that
are Syrian refugees,

01:09:59.700 --> 01:10:02.184
for example, if they've
dealt with a big struggle

01:10:02.184 --> 01:10:04.350
of that sort, how do you
deal with emotional issues.

01:10:04.350 --> 01:10:06.180
I think it's a lifelong process.

01:10:06.180 --> 01:10:08.390
It's not something I
anticipate that I will get over

01:10:08.390 --> 01:10:09.815
in three sessions with you.

01:10:09.815 --> 01:10:12.190
And that's why most of these
people do remain in therapy.

01:10:12.190 --> 01:10:15.080
People that came to our center
when it first opened in 1999,

01:10:15.080 --> 01:10:17.540
who are still seeing
our psychologists today,

01:10:17.540 --> 01:10:19.710
means that we're not
fixing it in one session.

01:10:19.710 --> 01:10:20.990
And it may never be fixed.

01:10:20.990 --> 01:10:24.540
Maybe just we've improved
upon these issues.

01:10:24.540 --> 01:10:27.470
So I think it requires lifelong
treatments with regards

01:10:27.470 --> 01:10:29.150
to the psychological issues.

01:10:29.150 --> 01:10:32.540
And for some people, maybe
lesser therapy than others.

01:10:32.540 --> 01:10:34.824
And we just have to tailor
it to fit the individual.

01:10:34.824 --> 01:10:36.276
- [iNAUDIBLE].

01:10:40.399 --> 01:10:41.690
- No, it doesn't become easier.

01:10:41.690 --> 01:10:44.106
And even after patients lose
tremendous amounts of weight,

01:10:44.106 --> 01:10:46.550
they may still
have significantly

01:10:46.550 --> 01:10:49.100
disordered thinking
as it relates

01:10:49.100 --> 01:10:50.780
to how they're
perceived, and how

01:10:50.780 --> 01:10:53.070
they navigate their daily life.

01:10:53.070 --> 01:10:53.870
Yes.

01:10:53.870 --> 01:10:56.110
So I think that I
am departing now.

01:10:56.110 --> 01:10:57.110
But it's been a delight.

01:11:00.400 --> 01:11:00.915
So yes.

01:11:00.915 --> 01:11:01.790
Well, thank you guys.

01:11:01.790 --> 01:11:02.715
Thanks for coming.

01:11:02.715 --> 01:11:05.220
I really appreciate it.

